Other classifications differ, primarily in how the various decapod orders are related, and whether they should be orders or families.

====Suprafamilial classification of the Treatise====
This is the older classification that combines those found in parts K and L of the &quot;Treatise on Invertebrate Paleontology&quot;, which forms the basis for and is retained in large part by classifications that have come later.

